Business Brief -- General Motors Corp.:
   Chevrolet Revises Program
   On Rebates Through May 4
Chevrolet also cut the incentives on some models. For
example, the rebate on the 1991 model Chevrolet Camaro is now
$500, compared with $750.
   Several incentives were eliminated. There is no longer a
rebate on the 1991 Chevrolet Corsica or the 1991 and 1992
Beretta or Caprice. Previously, buyers could get rebates of
as much as $1,000 on those models. Incentives were also
eliminated on certain trucks, such as the fullsize Blazer.
Previously, buyers could get a $1,500 rebate on the 1991
model.